The article discusses Arizona Governor Doug Ducey's support for President Trump's decision to call up the National Guard to assist the Border Patrol in securing the southern border. Governor Ducey emphasizes that protecting citizens is the government's fundamental responsibility and states that the border is not currently secure. He expresses gratitude for the administration's actions and welcomes the National Guard's support. Governor Ducey also addresses the challenges faced by border states and emphasizes the need for federal assistance in securing the border.